<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 08 at 7:07PM CDT  by NWS Lubbock</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Motley,
southwestern Hall and southeastern Briscoe Counties through 730 PM
CDT...
At 707 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Turkey. This storm was nearly stationary.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Turkey and Valley Schools.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
